    "type": "paragraph",
    "paragraph": {
      "rich_text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": {
            "content": "There is talk of the “African Kirra” being here, a long right hand sand bottom right that has featured in a few magazines and videos. Julian and I take a stroll down the beach to a place that it starts to bend and looks like it might harbour such a wave. The sun is doing that classic African thing at sunset; burning orange and expanding to seemingly twice the size. Or maybe it’s just that you’re able to stare right at it that makes it look so big. ",
            "link": null
          },
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          },
          "plain_text": "There is talk of the “African Kirra” being here, a long right hand sand bottom right that has featured in a few magazines and videos. Julian and I take a stroll down the beach to a place that it starts to bend and looks like it might harbour such a wave. The sun is doing that classic African thing at sunset; burning orange and expanding to seemingly twice the size. Or maybe it’s just that you’re able to stare right at it that makes it look so big. ",
